=======================
Control Flow Statements
=======================

- If Statement
  -------------
  - if we want to execute a block of statements only when an condition is true
  - Syntax
    if(<boolean value>){  // condition/variable
      // code
    }

- If else 
  --------
  - if we want to execute either of 2 block of statements depending on a condition
  - Syntax
    if(<boolean value>){  // condition/variable
      // code execute when condition is true
    } else {
      // code execute when condition is false
    }

- Nested if else 
  ---------------
  - when we want to check multiple conditions
  - if one condition is false then it moves to next condition block 
  - Syntax
    if (<condition 1>){
      // code
    } else if (<condition 2>){
      // code
    } else if (<condition 3>){
      // code
    } else {
      // code
    }
    
- Swith statement
  ---------------
  - similar to Nested if statements
  - We we want to choose 1 block of statement from multiple blocks
    depending upon equality comrision of the value of an variable
  - We can have any number of case blocks
  - case value must be same type as variable provided in switch expression
  - Case value must be unique
    - Duplicate value gives compile-time error
  - break statements should be provided after each case
    - if not then all statements that case will be executed
  - we can have a "default" block (optional)
    wihch run when non of the cases matches the variable value
    
  - Syntax
    switch(<variable>){
    case value1:
    //code
    break;  optional
    case value2:
    //code
    break //optional
    ....
    default:
    // default code
    }

